snippet.textDisplay: Painkillers might not work fully with the virus. But the painkillers stop parts of the virus from spreading. It only slows down the infection.
snippet.textOriginal: Painkillers might not work fully with the virus. But the painkillers stop parts of the virus from spreading. It only slows down the infection.

snippet.textDisplay: Exactly what part of the virus are you speaking of? I have never heard of such a claim... it would make painkillers more valuable than hydroxychloroquine and ivermectin, both of which have failed to show efficacy.
